Pre heat oven to 350F.
Grease two 9 inch cake pans.
Whisk the dry ingredients first - flour,cocoa powder,sugar,baking powder.
Mix all the wet ingredients together.
In a mixer add in the wet ingredients into the dry mixture.
Divide the batter equally between the 2 pans.
Bake for 30 mins and remove them out of the oven to cool.
To make the butter cream frosting beat the butter for 2 mins.
Add cream, dark chocolate and vanilla essence and beat for a minute.
Place one cake on the cake stand and cover with thick frosting.
Place the second cake on the first and spread the choco chips on the top.
Use a piping bag to make flowes on the top.
Refrigerate the cake for 30 mins before slicing.    